                <div id="featuretext">
                    <h3>ABOUT POIESIS</h3>
					<p>... pronounced 'poy-EY-sis', from Greek <i>&pi;&omicron;&iota;&epsilon;&sigma;&iota;&sigmaf;</i>, "making, creation, production", whence our word "poetry"</p>
                    <div class="column">
                        <em>Thinking on both sides of the brain.</em>
                        <br/>
                        We are obsessed with beauty; but then, we're also obsessed with order.  Unwilling to discard either the logical attitude developed during an 
                    </div>
                    <div class="column">
                        intense mathematical training, or a lifelong desire to be an artist, we've come to marry the two ways of thinking, for your benefit, as a designer and coder.
                    </div>
                    <div class="column">
                        <em>Motivated by perfection.</em>
                        Maybe perfection is unattainable, but it can be pursued.  We don't care to assume it can't be found just because we haven't found it yet.
                    </div>
                </div>
